    "description": "This is a mitigation for [a matplotlib issue](https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/issues/8423) that @lindsayad ran into and I reported upstream. Rather than using the 'classic' stylesheet (which sets *a lot* of [matplotlib config parameters](https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/blob/master/lib/matplotlib/mpl-data/stylelib/classic.mplstyle)), we just need to set these two matplotlib rc parameters to have correct-looking fonts. Ideally we wouldn't be using matplotlib's rcParam system at all for this, but unfortunately due to [matplotlib issue #6518](https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/issues/6518) this is the only way to ensure that we write plots with the computer modern mathtext fonts we want rather than the new dejavusans font that's the default in matplotlib 2.0.",
